granitectopguy Stonemark is not "building their reputation on a general misconception that all stone needs to be sealed." Their product doesn't need to be sealed at all. I'm not surprised that industry people, such as fabricators, many of whom sell competing products to Stonemark, misinterpret the product's benefits. They don't use a sealer. It's a special treatment that is applied in their factories that works inside the stone, not just on the surface. That's how they give that 15 year guarantee.




